<paragraph id="ED44F01E8A7DFFFBFF0C278EFA3FFF25" blockId="14.[151,1436,1941,2021]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1437,151,708]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="212" pageId="14" pageNumber="211">
<keyLead id="560A532B8A7DFFFBFF0C278EFA3FFF25" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="212" pageId="14" pageNumber="211">
1 Wing with R 
<subScript id="717FF25B8A7DFFFAFEC727BFFEC0F838" attach="left" box="[348,355,1956,1968]" fontSize="5" pageId="14" pageNumber="211">1</subScript>
vein short, terminating at or before midpoint of wing (
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7DFFFAFCF4278EFC0AF823" box="[879,937,1941,1963]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1657,1681]" captionTargetBox="[163,1436,309,1630]" captionTargetId="figure-97@6.[151,1436,309,1633]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Microphorella breviradia sp. nov. and M. macdonaldi sp. nov. (males). 1. Habitus of M. breviradia sp. nov., left lateral view. 2. Head of M. breviradia sp. nov., anterior view (CNC487231). 3. Wing of M. breviradia sp. nov., anterior view (CNC487241). 4. Abdomen of M. breviradia sp. nov., right lateral view (CNC1155716). 5. Head of M. macdonaldi sp. nov., anterior view (holotype). Abbreviations: bm-m—basal medial crossvein; cua—anterior cubital (=anal) cell; CuA+CuP— anterior branch of cubital vein + posterior branch of cubital vein; dm—discal medial cell; dm-m—discal medial crossvein; epand—epandrium; h—humeral crossvein; M1, M2, M4—medial veins; (R)—right; R1, R2+3, R 4+5 —radial veins; Sc—subcostal vein; v epand proc—ventral epandrial process." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536919" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536919/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="211">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); female syntergite 9+10 with acanthophorous setae (
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7DFFFAFF7227A9FEF6F84F" box="[233,341,1970,1992]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–18" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1513,1537]" captionTargetBox="[162,1424,190,1481]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1489]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 16–18. Female terminalia of Microphorella breviradia sp. nov. 16. Terminalia, dorsal view (CNC487214). 17. Terminalia, lateral view (CNC487214). 18. Spermatheca, lateral view (CNC487218). Abbreviations: cerc—cercus; st—sternite; tg—tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536945" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536945/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="211">Figs 16, 17</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7DFFFAFEC427A9FE3EF840" box="[351,413,1970,1992]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1657,1681]" captionTargetBox="[151,1419,849,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-300@14.[151,1436,849,1634]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 31–36. Female abdomens of the Microphorella breviradia, M. chiragra and M. acroptera species groups. 31. M. breviradia sp. nov., left lateral view. 32. M. breviradia sp. nov., dorsal view. 33. Microphorella sp. 1 (M. chiragra species group), left lateral view. 34. Microphorella sp. 1 (M. chiragra species group), dorsal view. 35. Microphorella sp. 8 (M. acroptera species group), left lateral view. 36. Microphorella sp. 8 (M. acroptera species group), dorsal view. Abbreviation: tg—tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536983" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536983/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="211">31, 32</figureCitation>
); male terminalia with right epandrial lamella greatly enlarged and comprising most of hypopygium in right lateral view (
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7DFFFAFEC627D4FE38F86C" box="[349,411,1999,2021]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1657,1681]" captionTargetBox="[163,1436,309,1630]" captionTargetId="figure-97@6.[151,1436,309,1633]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Microphorella breviradia sp. nov. and M. macdonaldi sp. nov. (males). 1. Habitus of M. breviradia sp. nov., left lateral view. 2. Head of M. breviradia sp. nov., anterior view (CNC487231). 3. Wing of M. breviradia sp. nov., anterior view (CNC487241). 4. Abdomen of M. breviradia sp. nov., right lateral view (CNC1155716). 5. Head of M. macdonaldi sp. nov., anterior view (holotype). Abbreviations: bm-m—basal medial crossvein; cua—anterior cubital (=anal) cell; CuA+CuP— anterior branch of cubital vein + posterior branch of cubital vein; dm—discal medial cell; dm-m—discal medial crossvein; epand—epandrium; h—humeral crossvein; M1, M2, M4—medial veins; (R)—right; R1, R2+3, R 4+5 —radial veins; Sc—subcostal vein; v epand proc—ventral epandrial process." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536919" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536919/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="211">Figs 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7DFFFAFE3F27D4FE1EF86C" box="[420,445,1999,2020]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1668,1692]" captionTargetBox="[156,1418,191,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-33@8.[151,1436,181,1644]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 10–15. Hypopygium of Microphorella breviradia sp. nov. 10. Hypopygium, left lateral view (CNC DIPTERA  192173). 11. Hypopygium, right lateral view (CNC DIPTERA  192173). 12. Right epandrial lamella, right lateral view (CNC DIPTERA  192167). 13. Right epandrial lamella, right lateral view (CNC487206). 14. Hypopygium and sternite 8, dorsal view (CNC DIPTERA  192173). 15. Right cercus, dorsal view (CNC487206). Abbreviations: cerc—cercus; d sur—dorsal lobe of surstylus; epand—epandrium; hypd—hypandrium; hyprct—hypoproct; (L)—left; pgt lb—postgonite lobe; ph—phallus; (R)—right; v epand proc—ventral epandrial process; v sur—ventral lobe of surstylus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536941" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536941/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="211">11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7DFFFAFE5D27D4FE42F86D" box="[454,481,1999,2021]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–21" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[154,1424,459,1815]" captionTargetId="figure-86@10.[151,1436,446,1825]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 19–21. Hypopygium of Microphorella vespera sp. nov. (CNC DIPTERA  105212). 19. Hypopygium, left lateral view. 20. Hypopygium, right lateral view. 21. Hypopygium and sternite 8, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cerc—cercus; d sur—dorsal lobe of surstylus; epand—epandrium; hypd—hypandrium; hyprct—hypoproct; (L)—left; pgt lb—postgonite lobe; ph—phallus; (R)—right; v epand proc—ventral epandrial process; v sur—ventral lobe of surstylus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536947" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536947/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="211">20</figureCitation>
), hypandrium reduced to narrow subtriangular band, only visible from left side of hypopygium (
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7DFFFBFAEA27D4FF5FFF25" captionStart="FIGURES 10–15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1668,1692]" captionTargetBox="[156,1418,191,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-33@8.[151,1436,181,1644]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 10–15. Hypopygium of Microphorella breviradia sp. nov. 10. Hypopygium, left lateral view (CNC DIPTERA  192173). 11. Hypopygium, right lateral view (CNC DIPTERA  192173). 12. Right epandrial lamella, right lateral view (CNC DIPTERA  192167). 13. Right epandrial lamella, right lateral view (CNC487206). 14. Hypopygium and sternite 8, dorsal view (CNC DIPTERA  192173). 15. Right cercus, dorsal view (CNC487206). Abbreviations: cerc—cercus; d sur—dorsal lobe of surstylus; epand—epandrium; hypd—hypandrium; hyprct—hypoproct; (L)—left; pgt lb—postgonite lobe; ph—phallus; (R)—right; v epand proc—ventral epandrial process; v sur—ventral lobe of surstylus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536941" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536941/files/figure.png" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="212" pageId="14" pageNumber="211">Figs 10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7CFFFBFE9D2083FEBCFF26" box="[262,287,152,174]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–21" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[154,1424,459,1815]" captionTargetId="figure-86@10.[151,1436,446,1825]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 19–21. Hypopygium of Microphorella vespera sp. nov. (CNC DIPTERA  105212). 19. Hypopygium, left lateral view. 20. Hypopygium, right lateral view. 21. Hypopygium and sternite 8, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cerc—cercus; d sur—dorsal lobe of surstylus; epand—epandrium; hypd—hypandrium; hyprct—hypoproct; (L)—left; pgt lb—postgonite lobe; ph—phallus; (R)—right; v epand proc—ventral epandrial process; v sur—ventral lobe of surstylus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536947" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536947/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">19</figureCitation>
)...................................................................... 
<emphasis id="DF8F2C0C8A7CFFFBFB1D2083FA3FFF25" bold="true" box="[1158,1436,151,173]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
<taxonomicName id="2AFB8B9D8A7CFFFBFB1D2083FAAFFF25" box="[1158,1292,151,173]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Microphorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviradia">
<emphasis id="DF8F2C0C8A7CFFFBFB1D2083FB38FF25" bold="true" box="[1158,1179,152,173]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="DF8F2C0C8A7CFFFBFB3C208CFAAFFF25" bold="true" box="[1191,1292,151,173]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">breviradia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED44F01E8A7CFFFBFF0C20AEFA3FFE8D" blockId="15.[151,1437,151,708]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
<keyLead id="560A532B8A7CFFFBFF0C20AEFA3FFE8D" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
- Wing with R 
<subScript id="717FF25B8A7CFFFBFEF920DFFECAFF58" attach="left" box="[354,361,196,208]" fontSize="5" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">1</subScript>
vein long, terminating beyond midpoint of wing (
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7CFFFBFCC520AEFC71FF43" box="[862,978,181,203]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1423,1447]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1399]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[151,1436,181,1399]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Males of the Microphorella chillcotti, M. acroptera and M. chiragra species groups. 25. Wing of M. chillcotti Brooks &amp; Cumming. 26. Abdomen of M. chillcotti Brooks &amp; Cumming, right lateral view. 27. Wing of M. acroptera Melander. 28. Abdomen of M. acroptera Melander, right lateral view. 29. Left hind leg of M. acroptera Melander, anterior view (arrow indicating spine-bearing tubercle on trochanter). 30. Abdomen of Microphorella sp. 15 (M. chiragra species group), right lateral view. Abbreviations: CuA+CuP—anterior branch of cubital vein + posterior branch of cubital vein; d sur s—dorsal lobe of surstylus seta; epand—epandrium; hypd—hypandrium; hypd proj—hypandrial projection; M2—second medial vein; R1—first radial vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536965/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Figs 25, 27</figureCitation>
); female syntergite 9+10 with acanthophorous spines (
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7CFFFBFEB720C9FE3DFF60" box="[300,414,210,232]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1657,1681]" captionTargetBox="[151,1419,849,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-300@14.[151,1436,849,1634]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 31–36. Female abdomens of the Microphorella breviradia, M. chiragra and M. acroptera species groups. 31. M. breviradia sp. nov., left lateral view. 32. M. breviradia sp. nov., dorsal view. 33. Microphorella sp. 1 (M. chiragra species group), left lateral view. 34. Microphorella sp. 1 (M. chiragra species group), dorsal view. 35. Microphorella sp. 8 (M. acroptera species group), left lateral view. 36. Microphorella sp. 8 (M. acroptera species group), dorsal view. Abbreviation: tg—tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536983" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536983/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Figs 33, 34</figureCitation>
); male terminalia with right epandrial lamella smaller than hypandrium in right lateral view, hypandrium large and reniform, visible from both left and right side of hypopygium (
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7CFFFBFC0120F4FB8FFE8E" box="[922,1068,239,262]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1423,1447]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1399]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[151,1436,181,1399]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Males of the Microphorella chillcotti, M. acroptera and M. chiragra species groups. 25. Wing of M. chillcotti Brooks &amp; Cumming. 26. Abdomen of M. chillcotti Brooks &amp; Cumming, right lateral view. 27. Wing of M. acroptera Melander. 28. Abdomen of M. acroptera Melander, right lateral view. 29. Left hind leg of M. acroptera Melander, anterior view (arrow indicating spine-bearing tubercle on trochanter). 30. Abdomen of Microphorella sp. 15 (M. chiragra species group), right lateral view. Abbreviations: CuA+CuP—anterior branch of cubital vein + posterior branch of cubital vein; d sur s—dorsal lobe of surstylus seta; epand—epandrium; hypd—hypandrium; hypd proj—hypandrial projection; M2—second medial vein; R1—first radial vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536965/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Figs 26, 28, 30</figureCitation>
)............................ 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="560FE8BB8A7CFFFBFF0C2116FA3FFD85" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
<paragraph id="ED44F01E8A7CFFFBFF0C2116FA3FFEF2" blockId="15.[151,1437,151,708]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
<keyLead id="560A532B8A7CFFFBFF0C2116FA3FFEF2" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
2 Wing with vein CuA 
<emphasis id="DF8F2C0C8A7CFFFBFE342116FE1CFEAA" box="[431,447,269,290]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">+</emphasis>
CuP absent; male wing with long apicoventral seta on hind margin (
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7CFFFBFBC62116FB04FEAB" box="[1117,1191,269,291]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1423,1447]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1399]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[151,1436,181,1399]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Males of the Microphorella chillcotti, M. acroptera and M. chiragra species groups. 25. Wing of M. chillcotti Brooks &amp; Cumming. 26. Abdomen of M. chillcotti Brooks &amp; Cumming, right lateral view. 27. Wing of M. acroptera Melander. 28. Abdomen of M. acroptera Melander, right lateral view. 29. Left hind leg of M. acroptera Melander, anterior view (arrow indicating spine-bearing tubercle on trochanter). 30. Abdomen of Microphorella sp. 15 (M. chiragra species group), right lateral view. Abbreviations: CuA+CuP—anterior branch of cubital vein + posterior branch of cubital vein; d sur s—dorsal lobe of surstylus seta; epand—epandrium; hypd—hypandrium; hypd proj—hypandrial projection; M2—second medial vein; R1—first radial vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536965/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
); male fore tibia and tarsomere 1 with row of posterior comb-like setae; male mid trochanter and mid femur each with strong basiventral seta; hypopygium with elongate medial hypandrial projection and dorsal surstylar lobe with strong sickle-shaped seta (
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7CFFFBFA9B215CFAEBFED5" box="[1280,1352,327,349]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1423,1447]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1399]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[151,1436,181,1399]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Males of the Microphorella chillcotti, M. acroptera and M. chiragra species groups. 25. Wing of M. chillcotti Brooks &amp; Cumming. 26. Abdomen of M. chillcotti Brooks &amp; Cumming, right lateral view. 27. Wing of M. acroptera Melander. 28. Abdomen of M. acroptera Melander, right lateral view. 29. Left hind leg of M. acroptera Melander, anterior view (arrow indicating spine-bearing tubercle on trochanter). 30. Abdomen of Microphorella sp. 15 (M. chiragra species group), right lateral view. Abbreviations: CuA+CuP—anterior branch of cubital vein + posterior branch of cubital vein; d sur s—dorsal lobe of surstylus seta; epand—epandrium; hypd—hypandrium; hypd proj—hypandrial projection; M2—second medial vein; R1—first radial vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536965/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
); female abdominal tergite 5 medially with some slender submarginal setae, tergite 6 mainly glaborous... 
<emphasis id="DF8F2C0C8A7CFFFBFB0E217EFA3FFEF2" bold="true" box="[1173,1436,356,379]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
<taxonomicName id="2AFB8B9D8A7CFFFBFB0E217EFAAEFEF2" box="[1173,1293,356,378]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Microphorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chillcotti">
<emphasis id="DF8F2C0C8A7CFFFBFB0E217EFB09FEF2" bold="true" box="[1173,1194,357,378]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="DF8F2C0C8A7CFFFBFB2D217FFAAEFEF2" bold="true" box="[1206,1293,356,378]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">chillcotti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED44F01E8A7CFFFBFF0C2198FA3FFD85" blockId="15.[151,1437,151,708]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
<keyLead id="560A532B8A7CFFFBFF0C2198FA3FFD85" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
- Wing with vein CuA 
<emphasis id="DF8F2C0C8A7CFFFBFE322198FE1AFE10" box="[425,441,387,408]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">+</emphasis>
CuP extending slightly beyond cell cua, sometimes faint (
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7CFFFBFC792199FB89FE10" box="[994,1066,386,408]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1423,1447]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1399]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[151,1436,181,1399]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Males of the Microphorella chillcotti, M. acroptera and M. chiragra species groups. 25. Wing of M. chillcotti Brooks &amp; Cumming. 26. Abdomen of M. chillcotti Brooks &amp; Cumming, right lateral view. 27. Wing of M. acroptera Melander. 28. Abdomen of M. acroptera Melander, right lateral view. 29. Left hind leg of M. acroptera Melander, anterior view (arrow indicating spine-bearing tubercle on trochanter). 30. Abdomen of Microphorella sp. 15 (M. chiragra species group), right lateral view. Abbreviations: CuA+CuP—anterior branch of cubital vein + posterior branch of cubital vein; d sur s—dorsal lobe of surstylus seta; epand—epandrium; hypd—hypandrium; hypd proj—hypandrial projection; M2—second medial vein; R1—first radial vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536965/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
); male wing without long apicoventral seta on hind margin; male fore tibia and tarsomere 1 without comb-like setae; male mid trochanter and mid femur each without strong basiventral seta; hypopygium without elongate medial hypandrial projection and dorsal surstylar lobe without strong sickle-shaped seta (
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7CFFFBFE0621C1FDAFFE78" box="[413,524,474,496]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1423,1447]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1399]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[151,1436,181,1399]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Males of the Microphorella chillcotti, M. acroptera and M. chiragra species groups. 25. Wing of M. chillcotti Brooks &amp; Cumming. 26. Abdomen of M. chillcotti Brooks &amp; Cumming, right lateral view. 27. Wing of M. acroptera Melander. 28. Abdomen of M. acroptera Melander, right lateral view. 29. Left hind leg of M. acroptera Melander, anterior view (arrow indicating spine-bearing tubercle on trochanter). 30. Abdomen of Microphorella sp. 15 (M. chiragra species group), right lateral view. Abbreviations: CuA+CuP—anterior branch of cubital vein + posterior branch of cubital vein; d sur s—dorsal lobe of surstylus seta; epand—epandrium; hypd—hypandrium; hypd proj—hypandrial projection; M2—second medial vein; R1—first radial vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536965/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Figs 28, 30</figureCitation>
); female abdominal tergite 5 or 6 usually with either stout median or stout marginal setae (
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7CFFFBFAE921C1FEBCFD85" captionStart="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1657,1681]" captionTargetBox="[151,1419,849,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-300@14.[151,1436,849,1634]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 31–36. Female abdomens of the Microphorella breviradia, M. chiragra and M. acroptera species groups. 31. M. breviradia sp. nov., left lateral view. 32. M. breviradia sp. nov., dorsal view. 33. Microphorella sp. 1 (M. chiragra species group), left lateral view. 34. Microphorella sp. 1 (M. chiragra species group), dorsal view. 35. Microphorella sp. 8 (M. acroptera species group), left lateral view. 36. Microphorella sp. 8 (M. acroptera species group), dorsal view. Abbreviation: tg—tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536983" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536983/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Figs 34, 36</figureCitation>
)............................................................................................. 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="560FE8BB8A7CFFFBFF0C220EFA3FFD4B" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
<paragraph id="ED44F01E8A7CFFFBFF0C220EFA3FFDED" blockId="15.[151,1437,151,708]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
<keyLead id="560A532B8A7CFFFBFF0C220EFA3FFDED" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
<specimenCount id="FBFD3B978A7CFFFBFF0C220EFEB0FDA3" box="[151,275,533,555]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" type="male">3 Male</specimenCount>
hind trochanter with spine-bearing tubercle (
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7CFFFBFD58220EFCA9FDA3" box="[707,778,533,555]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1423,1447]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1399]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[151,1436,181,1399]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Males of the Microphorella chillcotti, M. acroptera and M. chiragra species groups. 25. Wing of M. chillcotti Brooks &amp; Cumming. 26. Abdomen of M. chillcotti Brooks &amp; Cumming, right lateral view. 27. Wing of M. acroptera Melander. 28. Abdomen of M. acroptera Melander, right lateral view. 29. Left hind leg of M. acroptera Melander, anterior view (arrow indicating spine-bearing tubercle on trochanter). 30. Abdomen of Microphorella sp. 15 (M. chiragra species group), right lateral view. Abbreviations: CuA+CuP—anterior branch of cubital vein + posterior branch of cubital vein; d sur s—dorsal lobe of surstylus seta; epand—epandrium; hypd—hypandrium; hypd proj—hypandrial projection; M2—second medial vein; R1—first radial vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536965/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
); male terminalia with bare hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7CFFFBFB0C220EFB7CFDA3" box="[1175,1247,533,555]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1423,1447]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1399]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[151,1436,181,1399]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Males of the Microphorella chillcotti, M. acroptera and M. chiragra species groups. 25. Wing of M. chillcotti Brooks &amp; Cumming. 26. Abdomen of M. chillcotti Brooks &amp; Cumming, right lateral view. 27. Wing of M. acroptera Melander. 28. Abdomen of M. acroptera Melander, right lateral view. 29. Left hind leg of M. acroptera Melander, anterior view (arrow indicating spine-bearing tubercle on trochanter). 30. Abdomen of Microphorella sp. 15 (M. chiragra species group), right lateral view. Abbreviations: CuA+CuP—anterior branch of cubital vein + posterior branch of cubital vein; d sur s—dorsal lobe of surstylus seta; epand—epandrium; hypd—hypandrium; hypd proj—hypandrial projection; M2—second medial vein; R1—first radial vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536965/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
); female abdominal tergite 5 usually with cluster of stout median setae (
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7CFFFBFD7A2229FCF6FDC0" box="[737,853,562,584]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1657,1681]" captionTargetBox="[151,1419,849,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-300@14.[151,1436,849,1634]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 31–36. Female abdomens of the Microphorella breviradia, M. chiragra and M. acroptera species groups. 31. M. breviradia sp. nov., left lateral view. 32. M. breviradia sp. nov., dorsal view. 33. Microphorella sp. 1 (M. chiragra species group), left lateral view. 34. Microphorella sp. 1 (M. chiragra species group), dorsal view. 35. Microphorella sp. 8 (M. acroptera species group), left lateral view. 36. Microphorella sp. 8 (M. acroptera species group), dorsal view. Abbreviation: tg—tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536983" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536983/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Figs 35, 36</figureCitation>
), female abdominal tergite 6 without row of stout marginal setae......................................................................... 
<emphasis id="DF8F2C0C8A7CFFFBFB16224BFA3FFDED" bold="true" box="[1165,1436,591,613]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
<taxonomicName id="2AFB8B9D8A7CFFFBFB16224BFAAEFDED" box="[1165,1293,592,613]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Microphorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acroptera">
<emphasis id="DF8F2C0C8A7CFFFBFB16224BFB01FDED" bold="true" box="[1165,1186,592,613]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="DF8F2C0C8A7CFFFBFB35224BFAAEFDED" bold="true" box="[1198,1293,592,613]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">acroptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED44F01E8A7CFFFBFF0C2276FA3FFD4B" blockId="15.[151,1437,151,708]" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
<keyLead id="560A532B8A7CFFFBFF0C2276FA3FFD4B" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">
- Male hind trochanter without spine-bearing tubercle; male terminalia with setose hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7CFFFBFBEB2276FB1BFD0B" box="[1136,1208,621,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1423,1447]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1399]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[151,1436,181,1399]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Males of the Microphorella chillcotti, M. acroptera and M. chiragra species groups. 25. Wing of M. chillcotti Brooks &amp; Cumming. 26. Abdomen of M. chillcotti Brooks &amp; Cumming, right lateral view. 27. Wing of M. acroptera Melander. 28. Abdomen of M. acroptera Melander, right lateral view. 29. Left hind leg of M. acroptera Melander, anterior view (arrow indicating spine-bearing tubercle on trochanter). 30. Abdomen of Microphorella sp. 15 (M. chiragra species group), right lateral view. Abbreviations: CuA+CuP—anterior branch of cubital vein + posterior branch of cubital vein; d sur s—dorsal lobe of surstylus seta; epand—epandrium; hypd—hypandrium; hypd proj—hypandrial projection; M2—second medial vein; R1—first radial vein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536965/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
); female abdominal tergite 5 without cluster of stout median setae, female abdominal tergite 6 usually with row of stout marginal setae (
<figureCitation id="75C0EC9B8A7CFFFBFA842291FA2EFD28" box="[1311,1421,650,672]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1657,1681]" captionTargetBox="[151,1419,849,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-300@14.[151,1436,849,1634]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 31–36. Female abdomens of the Microphorella breviradia, M. chiragra and M. acroptera species groups. 31. M. breviradia sp. nov., left lateral view. 32. M. breviradia sp. nov., dorsal view. 33. Microphorella sp. 1 (M. chiragra species group), left lateral view. 34. Microphorella sp. 1 (M. chiragra species group), dorsal view. 35. Microphorella sp. 8 (M. acroptera species group), left lateral view. 36. Microphorella sp. 8 (M. acroptera species group), dorsal view. Abbreviation: tg—tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536983" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536983/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="212">Figs 33, 34</figureCitation>
).............................................................................. 
